radiographic_examinations.findings: Diffuse osteopenia with coarse trabecular changes of the long bones and thinning of the diaphyseal cortices but no fractures.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: On repeat skeletal survey at 17 months, osteopenia was greatly decreased, and no fractures or architectural abnormalities were detected, although metaphyseal sclerosis of the long bones was also noted.
